<item>
            <title>[POOL-348] The commons-pool-evictor-thread should run as a Deamon</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/POOL-348</link>
                <project id="12310488" key="POOL">Commons Pool</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The thread &quot;commons-pool-evictor-thread&quot; does not run as a Deamon and&#160;keeps the JVM alive when all other non Deamon threads has ended.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there any reason for this behaviour? Otherwise the thread should be started as a Deamon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13177599">POOL-348</key>
